{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"114df7da-fece-4ab9-a897-a22afd1fbec2","content":"The template.json is a good start but has a few issues before it's NuGet-ready:\n\n**Functional bug:**\n- The `Framework` symbol has no `replaces` property, so the user's choice will never be substituted into any file (e.g., the `.csproj`'s `<TargetFramework>`). It's a no-op parameter.\n\n**Missing recommended fields:**\n- **`$schema`** — Enables IDE validation. Should be `\"https://json.schemastore.org/template\"`.\n- **`groupIdentity`** — Required by NuGet conventions for template discovery/updates (e.g., `\"MyCompany.WebApi.CSharp\"`).\n- **`preferNameDirectory`** — Typically `true` for project templates.\n- **`defaultName`** — Fallback project name when the user doesn't supply `-n`.\n\n**Other observations:**\n- The template directory is empty — there are no actual source files (`.csproj`, `Program.cs`, etc.) to scaffold. A template package with no content won't be useful.\n- No `.nuspec` or `.csproj` for packing the template into a NuGet package exists yet.\n\n**Verdict:** Not ready to publish. Fix the `Framework` symbol wiring, add the missing metadata fields, and — most importantly — add the actual template source files and a packaging project.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2435d87a-88e8-480b-beb3-f0844f7ce952","outputTokens":322,"requestId":"A7C2:34550C:12C6D9D:151AD3A:6A027B78"},"id":"92b71332-88a6-4f2d-ba68-6cbc9ea69333","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:59:49.132Z","parentId":"ec61cf8c-6a6b-4aac-bafe-de5d58f72454"}
